buildModel

public void buildModel(java.lang.String modelFile,
                       int m,
                       int p,
                       int d)
Just wraps the buildTree method of the native classifier.

Parameters:
modelFile - The file containing the data. This file must contain a single column of floating point values. The model will be stored in a file with the same name but with the suffix .dmp appended to it.
m - Initial embedding dimension.
p - Number of principal components to use for final model.
d - Time delay in samples.
See Also:
NativeClassifier.buildTree(java.lang.String, int, int, int)

classify

Classifies the data in the buffer starting at the specified index.

Parameters:
index - The starting index in the buffer.
Returns:
The scores from each of the models. This will be an array containing the same number of values as there are models, and the order of the values correspond to the order of the models returned by getLoadedModelNames()
